This paper deals with 3D object tracking using LIDAR point clouds, which is a problem in computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves designing a Siamese tracker, which is a type of neural network architecture used in robotics (RO) and machine learning (LG). Additionally, the paper involves regularization techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (LG). Finally, the paper involves processing natural language text, which is a problem in computational linguistics (CL).
